# Application Architecture Flowchart

This flowchart outlines the "Agentic Data Analyst" pattern we discussed, showing how the user, the AI, and the database interact to provide fast, mathematically accurate answers from large CSV files.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as 🧑‍💻 User
    participant UI as 🖥️ Next.js Frontend
    participant API as ⚙️ Next.js API Route
    participant LLM as 🧠 LLM (Groq/Gemini)
    participant DB as 🦆 DuckDB (In-Memory)

    %% Step 1: Upload
    User->>UI: 1. Uploads CSV file (e.g., 10,000 rows)
    UI->>DB: 2. Loads CSV into memory
    DB-->>UI: 3. Returns Schema (Column Names) & 3 Sample Rows

    %% Step 2: Question
    User->>UI: 4. Asks: "What is the total revenue for Electronics?"
    
    %% Step 3: AI Code Generation
    UI->>API: 5. Sends Question + Schema
    API->>LLM: 6. Prompt: "Write SQL to answer this using these columns."
    Note over LLM: LLM does NOT see the 10,000 rows.<br/>It only sees the column names.
    LLM-->>API: 7. Returns SQL string: `SELECT SUM(revenue)...`

    %% Step 4: Execution
    API->>DB: 8. Executes SQL Query against 10,000 rows
    Note over DB: DuckDB processes all data<br/>instantly and accurately.
    DB-->>API: 9. Returns precise mathematical result (e.g., $1.2M)

    %% Step 5: Synthesis & Chart Data
    API->>LLM: 10. Prompt: "The answer is $1.2M. Format as chat text & chart JSON."
    LLM-->>API: 11. Returns JSON: { text: "...", chartData: {...} }
    
    %% Step 6: Render
    API-->>UI: 12. Sends JSON response
    UI-->>User: 13. Displays Chat Bubble & Renders Chart
```
